<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_cʼaldy" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
    <form type="lemma">
        <orth>cʼaldy</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>кухонный топор (в виде большого ножа с крючкообразно загнутым концом)</q>
        </cit>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>chopping axe (looking like a big knife with hook-shaped bent end)</q>
        </cit>
    </sense>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Усвоено из грузинского: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
            ><lang/><w>cʼaldi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                    ><lang/><w>cʼald</w><gloss><q>удлиненный топор с крюком</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="av"
            ><lang/><w>čalta</w><gloss><q>секира</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>šälti</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><w>šaltij</w><gloss><q>кинжал</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Происхождение тюркское?
        (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>čal-</w><gloss><q>бить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>резать</q></gloss></mentioned>, и пр.).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The word was borrowed from Georgian: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>cʼaldi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                    ><lang/><w>cʼald</w><gloss><q>long axe with a hook</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf.
        also <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>čalta</w><gloss><q>poleaxe</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>šälti</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>šaltij</w><gloss><q>dagger</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Turkic
        etymology? (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>čal-</w><gloss><q>beat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>cut</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc.).</etym>
</entry>
